org.linqs.psl.model.rule

Interface Rule

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AtomEvent.Listener, Cloneable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    UnweightedRule, WeightedRule
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractArithmeticRule, AbstractLogicalRule, AbstractRule, LogLoss, UnweightedArithmeticRule, UnweightedLogicalRule, WeightedArithmeticRule, WeightedLogicalRule

    public interface Rule
extends AtomEvent.Listener, Cloneable
    A template for functions that either constrain or measure the compatibility of the values of GroundAtoms.

    A Rule is responsible for instantiating GroundRules. A Rule must instantiate only WeightedGroundRules or only UnweightedGroundRules.

    Author:
    Matthias Broecheler , Eric Norris , Stephen Bach

    • Method Detail

      • groundAll

        void groundAll(AtomManager atomManager,
               GroundRuleStore grs)
        Adds all missing, potentially unsatisfied GroundRules to a GroundRuleStore based on an AtomManager.

        Specifically, will add any GroundRule templated by this Rule that satisfies all the following conditions:

        • The GroundRule has incompatibility or infeasibility greater than NumericUtilities.strictEpsilon for some assignment of truth values to the RandomVariableAtoms currently persisted in the AtomManager's Database given the truth values of the ObservedAtoms and assuming that any RandomVariableAtom not persisted has a truth value of 0.0.
        • The GroundRule is not already in the GroundRuleStore.
        • If the GroundRule is a WeightedGroundRule, its incompatibility is not constant with respect to the truth values of RandomVariableAtoms (including those not persisted in the AtomManager's Database).

        Only GroundRules which satisfy these conditions should be added.

        Parameters:
        atomManager - AtomManager on which to base the grounding
        grs - store for new GroundRules
        See Also:
        WeightedGroundRule.getIncompatibility(), UnweightedGroundRule.getInfeasibility()

      • registerForAtomEvents

        void registerForAtomEvents(AtomEventFramework eventFramework,
                           GroundRuleStore grs)
        Registers this Rule to listen for the AtomEvents it needs to update a GroundRuleStore.

        Specifically, this Rule will register for AtomEvents and update the GroundRuleStore in response to AtomEvents. In response to an AtomEvent on a RandomVariableAtom, the GroundRuleStore must contain the GroundRules that are functions of it which would have been added via groundAll(AtomManager, GroundRuleStore) given the current state of the AtomEventFramework's Database and assuming that the RandomVariableAtom was also persisted in the Database.

        Parameters:
        eventFramework - AtomEventFramework to register with
        grs - GroundRuleStore to update in response to AtomEvents

      • unregisterForAtomEvents

        void unregisterForAtomEvents(AtomEventFramework eventFramework,
                             GroundRuleStore grs)
        Stops updating a GroundRuleStore in response to AtomEvents from an AtomEventFramework and unregisters with that AtomEventFramework if it no longer needs to listen for AtomEvents from it.
        Parameters:
        eventFramework - AtomEventFramework to unregister with
        grs - GroundRuleStore to stop updating
